dcterms:description: Data 1 was obtained from a developed test bed built using a water tank with no disturbance. The dataset includes digital message signals passed through a quadrature phase shift keying (QPSK) modulation block, filtered, and sent over the underwater channel. The data collected at the transmitter and receiver were used as input and label for machine learning models.
dcterms:title: Data 1

dcterms:creator: R. Jiang
S. Cao
C. Xue
L. Tang
dcterms:description: Data 2 was collected from a lake, a natural body of water, with no artificial disturbance. The dataset includes transmitted symbols subjected to the same signal processing stages as Data 1, providing a real underwater dataset for evaluation.
dcterms:title: Data 2

dcterms:creator: R. Jiang
X. Wang
S. Cao
J. Zhao
X. Li
dcterms:description: Data 3 was collected using the same setup and parameters as Data 2, but with disturbance introduced to create a mild chaotic scenario. This dataset was used to evaluate the performance of deep learning models in a more challenging environment.
dcterms:title: Data 3
